# Customization

When you load a **UXDL** component and you've previously loaded the 
corresponding `uxdl.css` file, a basic style library will be added to 
the component.

To easy customize the different components that this library brings, 
we have provided two different methods, using **BEM Classes** 
and **CSS Custom Properties**.

## BEM Classes

We are always exporting CSS classes in our components and we use 
[BEM to decide the names](http://getbem.com) for each part of the component.

Example of BEM classes:

<!--<pre
  language="xml">
  <div className="uxdl-author uxdl-author--primary uxdl-author--rounded">
